dc9x1SR-617EuONRnoyGdNHjmJB4wHMkwjYZjxHvcaU0sJWMuAjytn_bp59qW2q6PDvt3s2Oeqc=
1Hm2Tg7SvKP2z48H2oH_3poGy9t7jW4ci0QlPZg3zLKW-pLz7JBgNRk20WVppJyzsdxFoKL9_LN=
FhXzNApOUSPb2FLhH_oDnxOP6Q], was built to win high-frequency DeFi use cases=
, and it=E2=80=99s in the lead there.=C2=A0
Flow=E2=80=99s wants to win by getting as many regular consumers, or =E2=80=
=9Cnormies,=E2=80=9D onboarded as possible.=C2=A0
That means starting with the strategy most people associate with Flow: work=
ing with global brands those consumers love like the NBA, NFL, UFC, La Liga=
, and Dr. Seuss.=C2=A0
Beyond IP holders, Flow seems to be tapping into huge pools of consumers vi=
a the tech giants; Google is an investor and a leak last month showed Insta=
gram is working on integrating Flow NFTs. There are also the beginnings of =
a very interesting developer ecosystem on Flow, with unicorns like PlayCo a=
nd Animoca building games on Flow alongside emerging success stories like G=
enies [https://email.mg-d1.substack.com/c/eJxFkEtuxCAQRE8z7GLxt1mwyCbXQHzaH=
jQ2OIAT-fZh7EUkBGo11dWvvG2w5HLqPdeG3pdp5w46wW9doTUo6KhQTAyaSDoxwRUKmimHJy9R=
rGYuAJuNq27lALQfbo3etpjTJcGYCvTUcsRT8HSaZxcc9m6cgDDCsXKWkImF29geIULyoOEHypk=
ToFU_W9vrg30-6Fc_C6QIdfB56wWKmmJKMcMjYYIKOdDBUR44gxAESDJLMczLKr7tcj443paPQI=
Z6uNqsf72HoKJTbi6XmJb-4fW0G6xXo3OY_m5Hiu00kKxbIdyI7Y7qgjZ9ISg9wmBs6wFxKWUHU=
kqqG6lnwNU0EiU56s4hd1X6N_0DOsyAhw] and Cryptoys [https://email.mg-d1.substa=
ck.com/c/eJxFkEtuhTAMRVfzMivKHzLIoJNuA-VjeFEhoYlpxe6bPgaVLFuWfXV1bnAIa6mXPU=
pD8tdmvA6wGX7aBohQydmgzilapvkklDQkWmE8nYImqc1LBdhd2izWE8hx-i0Fh6nkl4RSrsjTT=
sZH8NwvYxAg5TjysGhtvAYY46L4bezOmCAHsPAN9SoZyGafiEd7iPcH_-gV6nVgudqQSt9Ispxy=
TgUdmVBc6YEPnssoBcSoQLNFq2FZN_Xl1ush6b6-RTa00zd04XMIZSfV5oK-1JTX_vD5dDtsr0M=
Hmfvcz5zwmiE7v0G8GfHO6kU9r5Ch9gzj7LAnJLXWjE3GaHMz9RCkmUZmtCTdOZauyv-mv4Wrgb=
M].=C2=A0
Flow is targeting both today=E2=80=99s normies and the next generation of u=
sers and builders so web3-native they won=E2=80=99t even call it web3. One =
of Flow=E2=80=99s biggest hidden advantages is that it=E2=80=99s trying to =
onboard (and retain) all of the youngest users via Genies, Cyptoys, Brud, a=
nd a more seamless experience. Those young users will become creators and b=
uilders and whales. Building for them means Flow can play the long game.
That time horizon is the part that people not intimately familiar with Flow=
 miss. I missed it too.=C2=A0
When I started talking to the Flow team about potentially writing the piece=
, my assumption was that the Flow team had decided to approach the The Scal=
ability Trilemma [https://email.mg-d1.substack.com/c/eJxFUMFyhSAM_JrHrQ4goB=
w49NLfcBCiMkW0GF_Hv2_e89AZZpNAkmU3eIR5q5fbtwPZCwa8dnAFfo8MiFDZeUAdUnTCyL7Vy=
rLoWjvyPhiWjmGqAKtP2WE9ge3nmFPwmLbyHuFcara4NugwGtVZ60U39eF1H4UyylppjJhuYn_G=
BCWAgyfUayvAslsQ9-PRfj7kF51nQp_TdxM8FTMUqD5TJrkUFLh6QUdwLL7GVOZmwTWz5KhB8pZ=
3otVSm0Y2o1RRtRCjBqI3upnmrH_8fD0UX-ePKJrjHA_0gbi2lVVXNhy3Siup4XvxK-T3A-kdKK=
5nSXgNUPyYId5W4G3p25zh_itCHDySkcqQatFba-wtnbxStu-ENYoRc9xoqvyT_gFBD4u7] =E2=
=80=93 blockchains can only have two of three of Security, Decentralization=
, and Scalability =E2=80=93 by completely sacrificing Decentralization in e=
xchange for Scalability and Security.=C2=A0
Now I actually think they=E2=80=99re trying to solve the Trilemma without s=
acrificing any of the three by adding a fourth dimension: Time.
For Flow, the team re-thought how to build a blockchain that can handle com=
plex dapps serving billions of users from scratch. They realized that it mi=
ght be possible to solve the Trilemma by adding a bunch of complexity upfro=
nt, reducing decentralization in the short-term, and building a product and=
 ecosystem that achieves all three over time.=C2=A0
In other words, it=E2=80=99s impossible to solve the Trilemma with simple s=
olutions from day one, but it=E2=80=99s possible to do it if you relax the =
time constraint and =E2=80=9Cdecentralize=E2=80=9D progressively.=C2=A0
So what does that complexity look like?=C2=A0
Under the hood, Flow=E2=80=99s architects reimagined everything:=C2=A0
A new programming language =E2=80=93 Cadence =E2=80=93 that makes tokens th=
eir own resource type, which means developers can better build for and prot=
ect peoples=E2=80=99 money.=C2=A0
A new multi-node architecture, one that splits verification and compute and=
 splits nodes into four types: Consensus, Verification, Execution, and Coll=
ection.
Dapper provides a custodial wallet for newbies, but experienced users can b=
ring or build their own.=C2=A0
Over time, because the wallet keys cycle, users can choose to switch to non=
-custodial without transferring their assets whenever they=E2=80=99re ready=
=2E=C2=A0
A more sustainable blockchain, which Deloitte found [https://email.mg-d1.su=
bstack.com/c/eJxFkUGOhCAQRU_T7DQIiLJgMZu5hgEplTSCgzjG20_ZLiYh_KSg6n8eoykwp3=
zpLe2F3NtQrg10hHMPUApkcuyQB-90I1nPW6GI01xZ2o-S-H2YMsBqfNAlH0C2wwY_muJT_LRQy=
lqyaN6prpO8c7RruLW9tZy3itPeqUk0onuMzeE8xBE0_EK-UgQS9FLKtr_414t94zrPs05xCgkl=
z1i4-1DuSmVDGt_jYnys9mMvqMb64MtVQYQ8X5WDkDw-qcqwpVyqOBXiNaOMUX4Ha1kra1ZbJpz=
g4FwLsplkW09zaH_MfL0EXefKNfV-WJw_vusxrSTrmIpN2ccZL7wXs0L4HCCLAXU9ImYYANMEcA=
-m8uD-gBvmOx5-gxtMQchCStk0vVJSPViQo1B91ygpCDq7hF3x3_QPqNiaKg] takes less en=
ergy than an Instagram post.
Flow has decentralized in a slow, progressive fashion. They aren=E2=80=99t =
in a rush. They=E2=80=99re building for the next billion users, the mainstr=
eam users.=C2=A0
Building for the mainstream means making different trade-offs in the short-=
term in pursuit of the long-term vision, and it means making Flow the most =
welcoming place for the next generation of builders to build rich, composab=
le experiences. That takes time.
Taking time is a risky play, and one that=E2=80=99s in no way guaranteed to=
 pay off in such a fast-moving environment, but if it works, it has the cha=
nce to make Flow the first blockchain with real, =E2=80=9Coh shit everyone =
is using this,=E2=80=9D network effects.=C2=A0
It=E2=80=99s hard to bet against the Flow team. They=E2=80=99ve been throug=
h the Hype Cycle a couple times now, and they just keep building and attrac=
ting millions of users. At this point, four years into Dapper Labs and less=
 than 18 months into Flow=E2=80=99s public life, we might not even need to =
wait that long to see liftoff. Flow is finding its rhythm.=C2=A0
For example, remember that transaction cool down we talked about a few para=
graphs ago? Flow=E2=80=99s already bounced back. It=E2=80=99s picking up st=
eam.=C2=A0
There were 3x more Flow transactions last month than there were in Septembe=
r, in the midst of an NFT bear market. Overall, Flow has handled more NFT t=
ransactions than any other chain by far.=C2=A0
But its ambition is to be more than an NFT chain. It=E2=80=99s building the=
 =E2=80=9Cblockchain for open worlds.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
Layne Lafrance, Flow co-founder and Product Lead, explained that =E2=80=9CF=
low is designed to be performant when people come together, build together,=
 build on top of things. Complex communities need to be able to evolve.=E2=
=80=9D=C2=A0
To that end, in October, Dapper acquired Brud [https://email.mg-d1.substack=
=2Ecom/c/eJxFkMuOhCAQRb-m2WmQl7JgMZv5DcOj=
2iatYAOO8e8HdZJJKlSFy82ljtUFppgOtcZc=
0HmM5VhBBdjzDKVAQluGNHqnOkEGyplETlFp8GAF8nl8JoBF-1mVtAFaNzN7q4uP4bJgTDh6KUu=
5Zsw50dMBEwdUd7I3wpJBg-wHeQfrzXkIFhT8QDpiADSrVylrftCvB_mute976_S6Qpq1ya2NS7=
08v5riNd5ac4qNtp_NJ8iNSZtDXhFMCKa47ygnXLSkNYQ5RsE5DqJ7Ct4-p5l_9HQ8GF6mxnVt3=
kwu2r7PIJRUiMXE5MNUH7xfeoH5EurOY-3LFnw5RgjazOBuHOXGegEaJwiQKm436lJhMiFE1w1S=
ir_1Ky8mh76TgqGa7GJ1hf_QX0QMkTo], the team behind virtual celebrity Lil Miq=
uela helmed by Trevor McFedries, who also founded popular DAO Friends with =
Benefits (FWB [https://email.mg-d1.substack.com/c/eJxFkMtuxCAMRb9m2BXxCgMLF=
t30NyIIToKGQAqkUf6-dLKoZNmy_Lg6d7INllwus-fa0F8a27WDSXDWCK1BQUeFMgZvqGSKD0Ij=
b7h2RE0ShTrOBWCzIZpWDkD74WKYbAs5vU8IYQNajZqVIIxZUNIJpdXMn54RyZWjMyWO3sL28AH=
SBAZ-oFw5AYpmbW2vD_75YF89zvPE8-nwCnHvLQqG9beEkyflAxskZtgx4QUH7weQdJYDnpc4fN=
vlegiyLR-e4nq42uz0wlPeUDEpN5dLSEtfeK12g_gedJKx1-1IoV0jJOsi-Buy3Wa9sccFEpRuo=
h9t6xYJKSWlSmupb6jugtDqSbUUqCv73K_Sv-gvkMGAlA]). Trevor will be running Dap=
per=E2=80=99s push into DAOs on Flow, dubbed Dapper Collectives, starting w=
ith Brud DAO.=C2=A0
I asked Trevor when we=E2=80=99ll see Brud DAO, and his answer encapsulates=
 the way that Dapper builds: =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re doing it as soon as pos=
sible, but the motto here is the anti-Facebook: Move Slow and Get it Right.=
=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
=E2=80=9CWe could be wrong,=E2=80=9D Roham admitted, =E2=80=9CBut if we=E2=
=80=99re right, this is the way to build new mainstream consumer products.=
=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
There=E2=80=99s no guarantee they get it right. Looking at Flow=E2=80=99s m=
arket cap compared to other L1s, the money suggests that people think it=E2=
=80=99s unlikely. But the Flow team has been patiently snapping LEGO blocks=
 together in pursuit of a big, long-term vision, and they know better than =
anyone how to bring consumers into web3. It=E2=80=99s worth understanding w=
hat they=E2=80=99re up to:=20
